account.description: The ID of the account in which you ran this execution.

atomId.description: The ID of the Runtime the on which the process ran.

atomName.description: The name of the Runtime on which the process ran.

executionDuration.description: The number of milliseconds it took to run the process.

executionTime.description: The start date and time this run.

executionType.description:
Indicates how initiation of the process run occurred. Possible values are:
- *exec*\_*listener* \(run initiated by a listener request\)
- *exec*\_*manual* \(manual run\)
- *exec*\_*sched* \(scheduled run\)
- *retry*\_*manual* \(manual retry\)
- *retry*\_*sched* \(scheduled retry\)
- *sub*\_*process* \(subprocess call\)
- *test*\_*manual* \(test mode run\)

inboundDocumentCount.description: The number of processed inbound documents.

inboundDocumentSize.description: The aggregate size in bytes of the processed inbound documents.

inboundErrorDocumentCount.description: The number of processed inbound documents with errors.

launcherID.description:
The API Service component that kicks off the run.

**Note:** The Runtime must have the **API Type** set to **Advanced** on the **Shared Web Server** tab of **Runtime Management** to specify the launcherID.

message.description: Any error message returned from the run.

nodeId.description: The ID of the Molecule node in which the run occurred for a process run in a Runtime cluster or Runtime cloud. For a run occurring in a Runtime, this field is omitted.

originalExecutionId.description: The original execution ID, if this execution is a retry.

outboundDocumentCount.description: The number of processed outbound documents.

outboundDocumentSize.description: The aggregate size in bytes of the processed outbound documents.

parentExecutionId.description: The ID of the run of the parent process, if this run and the parent processâ€™ run were both subprocesses.

processId.description: The ID of the run process.

processName.description: The name of the run process.

recordedDate.description: The end time when the process execution completes.

reportKey.description:
The web service user that authenticated to make the run request.

**Note:** For Runtimes with an Authentication Type of External Provider, the reportKey is the API Key. Otherwise, it is the specified user name.

status.description:
The status of the run. Possible values are:
- *ABORTED*
- *COMPLETE*
- *COMPLETE*\_*WARN*
- *DISCARDED*
- *ERROR*
- *INPROCESS*
- *STARTED*

topLevelExecutionId.description: The ID of the run of the top-level process, if this run is a subprocess.
